      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Another step in the pentose phosphate pathway for degrading sugars (see Problem 29-21) is the conversion of ribose 5-phosphate to glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate. What kind of organic process is occurring? Propose a mechanism for the conversion.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdDhaIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--2f21c5d3a5d100ca4597617c9e9bb5b8088f9a82/OChem_29_EC_006.jpg\" alt=\"Ribose-5-phosphate reacts to form glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate and an aldehyde connected to a methylene linked to a phosphate group. Both structures are presented in Fischer projection.\">",
